Sentencas: CoFe2O4 has been demonstrated as a potential spinel coating for protecting the Cr-containing ferritic interconnects.
Titulo: CoFe2O4 spinel protection coating thermally converted from the electroplated Co-Fe alloy for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect application

Sentencas: This spinel had an electrical conductivity of 0.85 S cm(-1) at 800 degrees C in air and an average coefficient of thermal expansion (CTE) of 11.80 x 10(-6) K-1 from room temperature to 800 degrees C. A series of Co-Fe alloys were co-deposited onto the Crofer 22 APU ferritic steel via electroplating with an acidic chloride Solution.
Titulo: CoFe2O4 spinel protection coating thermally converted from the electroplated Co-Fe alloy for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect application

Sentencas: After thermal oxidation in air at 800 degrees C, a CoFe2O4 spinel layer was attained from the plated Co0.40Fe0.60 film.
Titulo: CoFe2O4 spinel protection coating thermally converted from the electroplated Co-Fe alloy for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect application

Sentencas: Furthermore, a channeled Crofer 22 APU interconnect electrodeposited with a 40-mu m Co0.40Fe0.60 alloy film as a protective coating was evaluated in a single-cell configuration.
Titulo: CoFe2O4 spinel protection coating thermally converted from the electroplated Co-Fe alloy for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect application
CoFe2O4 spinel protection coating thermally converted from the electroplated Co-Fe alloy for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect application

Sentencas: Cr-free CoFe2O4 spinel layer was effective in blocking the Cr migration/transport and thus contributed to the improvement in cell performance stability.
Titulo: CoFe2O4 spinel protection coating thermally converted from the electroplated Co-Fe alloy for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect application
